Build ubuntu-oracular sdcard for orangepi 5 plus:

Input files: ../rootfs-ubuntu-oracular/linaro-rootfs.img
                                      /linaro-esp.img

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin NVME-SSD/sdcard/emmc/USB2-SATA-SSD to SBC.
Run setup
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check if Ubuntu is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg glmark2-es2-x11 glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc snapd

sudo snap install mpv

speedtest-cli

glmark2-es2-wayland
glmark2-es2

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select hdmi0 as default )

Chromium -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' hyUhEjtlDLA -o avemaria.mp4
mpv avemaria.mp4
